|NPCID|67268| |NAME|Sanoriak| |LVL|Rank 2.3| |ABIL|136333,33975,132666,135237,135236| |ST|(npc:67268), formerly a Rank 1 brawl in Warlords of Draenor, is a Molten Core flamewalker that casts a wide array of fire-based spells that fortunately are all interruptible.<br/><br/>First priority is to either interrupt or avoid taking too much damage from (spell:132666), as one or two ticks will kill you. The (spell:33975) and (spell:136333) doesn't do enough damage to kill you, but you can interrupt either to reduce incoming damage. Otherwise, this is a simple fight. Interrupt, stun, mitigate, whatever gets the trick done, or feel the flames embrace!|	
|NPCID|115645| |NAME|Master Paku| |LVL|Rank 2.4| |ABIL|229865,229843,229918,229884| |ST|(npc:115645), a reference to Pac-Man, (Pakkuman in Japanese; an arcade game developed by Namco in 1980), bears much resemblance to the old (npc:67451) fight, where you need to navigate through a blue maze, this time made of water (like the blue maze in the game).<br/><br/>You need to collect golden (spell:229884)s around the maze to break (spell:229843), which reflects any incoming damage, and force (npc:115645), that is split into three, to enter (spell:229865). If you come into contact with the maze, you will get killed by (spell:229918). When the brawl starts, you will automatically start moving forward. You can cast while running and you can enable walk-mode if it's moving too fast for you.|	
|NPCID|117145| |NAME|Doomflipper| |LVL|Rank 3.1| |ABIL|| |ST|(npc:117145) is a huge "manatee" that is here to "seal the deal" with a strong melee attack. This is a straight up tank and spank brawl.|	
|NPCID|70736| |NAME|Splat| |LVL|Rank 3.2| |ABIL|133302| |ST|(npc:70736), formerly a Challenge Card brawl in Warlords of Draenor, is an ooze with huge health, fast (spell:141034) creating new copies of itself, increased damage compared to his predecessor (npc:67594), and the original (npc:70736) leaves a contrail of (spell:141036) to avoid.<br/><br/>The fight is pretty easy for casters able to move while casting since (npc:70736) and its copies move really, really slow, so just kite them around while dishing out the pain.|	
|NPCID|116743| |NAME|Shadowmaster Aameen| |LVL|Rank 3.3| |ABIL|232510,232504| |ST|(npc:116743) is a shadow caster and will keep casting (spell:232510) and (spell:232504). (spell:232504) leaves behind a pulsing shadow torch. (spell:232510) creates a blast of shadowy energy that moves forward to the recently spawned shadow torch. Upon reaching the torch, shadow blasts chain to all other torches, dealing shadow damage to any enemy it passes through.<br/><br/>Kite (npc:116743) slowly around and avoid standing between torches. It's a good idea to drop the torches not too far apart, as it quickly cuts off large areas of the arena. Don't worry, you two will have a blast!|	
|NPCID|115058| |NAME|Johnny Awesome| |LVL|Rank 3.4| |ABIL|205567,229139,229127,229111| |ST|This famous Blood Elf has been seen in Hillsbrad, Illidan's flashback to the Black Temple, Feralas, Firelands and more! (npc:115058) fights you accompanied by his pet (npc:54288). He will do normal (spell:205567) at you, (spell:229139), and channel a (spell:229127).<br/><br/>Additionally, you will have to avoid rain of arrows indicated by green circles on the ground. (npc:54288) does a charge stun if you get too far away from it. Use (spell:229127) to have (npc:115058) kill (npc:54288) and he will cast (spell:229111), taking increased damage while channeling.|	
|NPCID|115023| |NAME|Burnstachio| |LVL|Rank 4.1| |ABIL|229025,228981,228977,228988| |ST|(npc:115023) covers the arena in fire patches and cloaks himself in (spell:229025). Raining clouds clear patches through the maze and you need to move with the openings while dealing damage to (npc:115023).<br/><br/>You can pick up a (spell:228977) that gives you a (spell:228981), which also allows you to damage (npc:115023) and move safely on the fire for a short period of time before it falls off and you need to go pick it up again. If you stand on any of the fire patches, you get hit by (spell:228988) and die. Do not move when you spawn into the ring; you entry point is safe, but fire will spawn all around you and potentially kill you before you even get started.|	
|NPCID|67573| |NAME|Meatball| |LVL|Rank 4.2| |ABIL|134850,134851,134911| |ST|(npc:67573), formerly a Rank 4 brawl in Warlords of Draenor, is one of the funnier brawls you'll encounter. He has a debuff called (spell:134850), which forces him to spawn little purple orbs on the ground when you hit him. Picking these up grants you a buff called (spell:134851) -- stacking up to 50 times. (npc:67573) has a substantial health pool, impossible to chew through without the stacks of (spell:134851).<br/><br/>The only thing you have to do to beat him is to collect the orbs scattered on the ground (you simply walk over them). A short while into the brawl (npc:67573) will get (spell:134911), making the fight significantly harder and almost impossible if you do not have him near death or good defensive cooldowns available. (npc:67573)'s belly feels funny and is making loud gurgly noises. When you get him low, around 20%, he will explode into a puddle on the ground. It appers that (npc:67573) had eaten (npc:68475), which is also the cause of his (spell:134850) effect. (npc:68475) will take his leave by casting (spell:134917).|	
|NPCID|67488| |NAME|Max Megablast| |LVL|Rank 4.3| |ABIL|133162,133154,133249,133212| |ST|GG Engineering, formerly a Rank 7 brawl in Warlords of Draenor, is a goblin and gnome engineering duo with each their own special ability. (npc:67488) casts (spell:133212) indicated by a large red circle on the ground and (npc:67487) casts (spell:133172).<br/><br/>They both have access to an (spell:133162) that teleports them to a (npc:67500) that has (spell:133154), providing whoever is beneath it (you and engineering duo alike) the (spell:133249) buff.<br/><br/>The trick is to utilize the (spell:133212) cast by (npc:67488) to add extra damage to (npc:67487) and, if possible, himself as well. Stay on top of (npc:67487) the entire time and the rockets will do most of the damage for you. Remember to avoid the rockets yourself!|	
