|NPCID|71085| |NAME|Razorgrin| |LVL|Rank 5.2| |ABIL|142700,141598| |ST|Although it's "just" a huge shark spawned up on land, (npc:71085) has definitely earned his title <Terror of the High Seas>. Flopping around on the ground, (npc:71085) will slowly (spell:142700) his way towards you, eager and desperate to sink a mouth full of teeth into your flesh. A shark away from the comfortable depths of the ocean, how menacing and terrorfying could he be? Well, the shark has been menacing and terrorfying in waters (for over a decade!), and since patch 5.3, clearly, above waters as well. This is a relatively easy fight for ranged, but melee have to circle around it to attack it from the back or sides as a single (spell:141598) from the front will be the end of you.|	
|NPCID|67515| |NAME|Fleasy| |LVL|Rank 5.3| |ABIL|133157,133171| |ST|The Leper Gnome Quintet consists of (npc:67515), (npc:67514), (npc:67513), (npc:67516), and (npc:67511). These all apply the stackable debuff (spell:133157), that will slowly eat away your health pool.<br/><br/>You may need to kite them around to reduce the amount of stacks you get or get it to drop completely. You can make use of class specific defensive cooldowns to drop the stack, i.e. (spell:45438), (spell:642) or similar. High cleave damage is good and roots, slows, and pets allows you easier management of the debuff.|	
