|NPCID|70068| |NAME|Ahoo'ru| |LVL|Special| |ABIL|138845,138847,138802,138901,142585,142621,142624| |ST|(npc:70068), formerly the end Rank 7 brawl in Warlords of Draenor, is a two phase encounter, for which you still have to kill him in under two minutes. He starts out by spawning and then puts on a (spell:138901) with three charges that you will have to break through; kind of like what you do in Trial of the Champion or the dailies at the Argent Tournament Grounds.<br/><br/>Phase one consists of little shiny (npc:70066) that spawn around the room and move around slowly. You need to dodge these as they hit for about 200k. (npc:70068) will cast a flash of light towards these sparks making them extra sparkly and you need to run over and touch these, which will spawn an (npc:70081). Bring these angels to half health and they will start to channel (spell:138845). Run to (npc:70068), wait for the cast to complete, then run away before the (npc:70081) reaches (npc:70068) (so the charge hits him and doesn't kill you). Each charge reduces (npc:70068)'s shield stack by one. Do this three times and phase 2 will begin.<br/><br/>In Phase two the arena will be cleared from all the floating lights and you need to burn down (npc:70068). Besides his normal melee attacks, there are two noticeable mechanics that you need to be aware of. First, he will be casting a (spell:142621) that is interruptable, and secondly, he will summon a (spell:142585) around you (much like the Anima Ring on Dark Animus) that you need to run out of while hitting the least amount of orbs as they each apply a stacking debuff, ticking for large amounts of damage. He also randomly does a knockback and hits you with (spell:142624). Good luck!<br/><br/>If you can cope with the damage it is a good idea to spawn all three (npc:70081)s needed in Phase 1 and burst them down to enter Phase 2 faster, giving you more time to kill (npc:70068).|	
|NPCID|67588| |NAME|Akama| |LVL|Special| |ABIL|136194,126209,79797,139963| |ST|(npc:67588), formerly a Rank 2 brawl in Warlords of Draenor, has reappeared from the Black Temple with shaman abilities: he summons (spell:136194), uses (spell:126209), and casts (spell:79797) and (spell:139963). Interrupt the (spell:139963). Purge, dispel or spellsteal (spell:126209) if you can. You don't have to kill the (spell:136194), but if you can cleave them down you should. Other then that the fight is quite easy.|	
|NPCID|70977| |NAME|Anthracite| |LVL|Special| |ABIL|141369,142400,141403,141624,141415,141371,141496| |ST|(npc:70977), formerly a Legacy challenge in Warlords of Draenor, spawns (spell:141369), causing him to do significant ticking damage through (spell:142400) every second as long as the buff is active and causing him to retaliate with (spell:142400) every time he is struck. Attacking him in this state is a very quick way to kill yourself. He will also occasionally (spell:141403) patches at you; do not stand in these.<br/><br/>When the fight begins, you get a special action button with one use of (spell:141415). This shoots a jet of water out behind you on (npc:70977) causing him to be (spell:141371) and take 50% additional damage and stunning him for a few seconds. Pop your potions and cooldowns during this time to maximize damage. To use the spray more than once, you will have to kill adds called (npc:71048) that spawn throughout the arena. When they die, they will leave a cloud of mist granting you (spell:141496). Walking through it will give you another use of the spray to cool down (npc:70977).<br/><br/>Utilize survival cooldowns outside of the (spell:141371) phase to kill (npc:71048) and get another use of (spell:141415) through (spell:141496); rinse and repeat. With the additional damage he takes, some classes, with enough gear, will be able to burst him down in one round. Beware, (npc:71048) will extinguish if they path over the fire patches. Also, note that you need to have your back to (npc:70977) when you use the spray. The spray shoots out three projectiles that each go 8 yards. You must hit (npc:70977) with one of these for it to extinguish him.|	
|NPCID|116855| |NAME|Ash'katzuum| |LVL|Special| |ABIL|232831| |ST|(npc:116855), a reference to Ash Ketchum from Pokmon, continually casts (spell:232831) that spawns a wide array of (npc:116857)s from the center of the arena. These (npc:116857)s roam around and if you come in contact with any, they hit you for a very large amount of damage. Dodge the (npc:116857)s, which will be increasingly difficult the longer the fight goes on.|	
|NPCID|67424| |NAME|Battletron| |LVL|Special| |ABIL|133018,133015,133038| |ST|(npc:67424), formerly a Rank 7 brawl in Warlords of Draenor, is a construct that is (spell:133018), seven in total, that each detonate when you or a spell travels through it. It will (spell:133015) again if there are 4 or less active mines remaining. The trick is to kill a few mines and then damage through the open window. (npc:67424) will also cast (spell:133038) on you throughout the fight. As a caster, if you have any abilities, glyphs or talents that allow you to cast while moving, this will benefit you greatly in besting this energetic automatron, as stopping to cast heals to cover the damage from the orbs is ill-advised. The mines do not explode while (npc:67424) is summoning them, so this can be used to your advantage initially as well as mid-fight.|	
|NPCID|115354| |NAME|Beat Box| |LVL|Special| |ABIL|229215,229323,229578,229585| |ST|(npc:115354) does (spell:229215) as the first phase of the fight. You need to dodge a sequence of electrical patterns on the floor, i.e. one half covered, second half covered, middle free. Afer you complete the sequence (npc:115354) will start casting (spell:229323) and you will get ported to one of four (4) dancing circles around him, the camera angle will shift focus and you will view the arena from above, you will begin to dance and be unable to cast any spells or use any abilities.<br/><br/>Time to show off your (spell:229578) in this second phase! You now have to collect and dodge orbs to both deal damage to (npc:115354) and avoid damaging or killing yourself. Use the arrow keys to move between the four (4) positions (up, down, left, right). Collect as many light orbs as you can and avoid all the shadow orbs. Each collected light orb deals damage to (npc:115354) and every missed light orb deals damage to you through (spell:229585). Collecting any of the shadow orbs kills you. After a short period of time you need to start dodging (spell:229215) again to get back into collecting orbs. I hope your levels of funk are sufficient!|	
|NPCID|70694| |NAME|Big Badda Boom| |LVL|Special| |ABIL|140995,140996| |ST|(npc:70694), formerly a Rank 5 brawl in Warlords of Draenor, is a huge Bombling and is likely a reference to movie The Fifth Element starring Milla Jovovich playing Leeloo; crashing into Korben Dallas' taxi she goes "Big Badda Boom". (npc:70694) has only a weak melee attack. After you damage it some, it will (spell:140995) and split into slighty smaller (npc:70727)s; this (spell:140996) hurts a bit more than the melee.<br/><br/>As you damage the new mobs, they too will explode and split into (npc:70728)s. This continues several times until you end up facing a whole bunch of very tiny (npc:70729)s, approximately 54 in total. To meet the DPS requirement you will have to AoE, but AoEing down the bombs causes the explosions to all go off at once and thus hurt quite a bit, so be careful and make clever use of your survival cooldowns!<br/><br/>Knockbacks, bleeds, damage over time effects, snares, and immobilization effects can be a huge help to reduce the overall damage you will take from (spell:140996). Heal up between them if you can, use survival cooldowns when there are many bombs about to pop, and ask a spectating or brawling warlock to supply a healthstone to top you off if things get dire.|	
|NPCID|67678| |NAME|Blat| |LVL|Special| |ABIL|133302| |ST|(npc:67594) is a blob that keeps making copies of himself as the fight goes on. There is no reason to damage the copies, as your only objective is to kill the original, but you can cleave them down to mitigate damage taken. Kiting might not be essential, but reduces the overall damage you will take from (npc:67594) and his growd of copies. Don't let the copies overwhelm you, kite when possible, and this should be an easy fight. (npc:67594) also moves faster than his copies, so backpedaling a bit allows you to pick him out more easily and reduce the overall damage taken.|	
|NPCID|70794| |NAME|Blind Hero| |LVL|Special| |ABIL|141190,141189,141192| |ST|This is a high ranked Card Challenge fight back in Warlords of Draenor. The (npc:70794) will perform his (spell:141190) and (spell:141189) in random directions. These are frontal cone attacks that you either circle around as melee or outrange as a caster. After a few of these strikes he will start to channel (spell:141192), which is roughly a 20 yard aoe hit that you need to outrange. The fight is fairly simple in design, and compared to Mingus Diggs you might even be able to do it blindfolded!|	
|NPCID|70740| |NAME|Blingtron 3000| |LVL|Special| |ABIL|141359,141059,141229| |ST|(npc:70740) will spawn in one corner of the arena and casts (spell:141359), indicated by a red circle targeting your current location. Every so often, a small (npc:70802) will spawn from the gold pile next to (npc:70740), and immediately run straight to you. These mobs have about small amount of health, and "killing" them causes them to be stunned at 1 hp at the spot that you "killed" them.<br/><br/>What you need to do is form a chain of these mobs from (npc:70740)'s corner to that of the (npc:70743) in the opposite corner, so when you activate it it will get (spell:141059) and send an electrical surge back to him via the little Blingtrons. Receiving the shock from the tesla will cause (spell:141229) and increase (npc:70740)'s damage taken by 900% and stun him, preventing him from doing anything except standing there and taking the punishment! Form a line of 7-8 of the small adds, activate the tesla, and burn down (npc:70740) using all your cooldowns.<br/><br/>Beware, the electricity can jump to you and kill you (unless you are super conductive), so when you active the tesla, steer clear of the line you've formed.|	
|NPCID|67262| |NAME|Bruce| |LVL|Special| |ABIL|135342| |ST|Chomp chomp chomp! Woo hoo! You got Bruced! (npc:67262), formerly a Rank 5 brawl in Warlords of Draenor, is a crocodile who periodically casts (spell:135342). You either need to stun him or move away from his mouth when this happens or suffer the humiliating taunts from the spectators. It has a short cast time, and then channels, giving you enough time to move out of the way -- the best way to get out of trouble is to strafe to the side or circle around to the back.|	
|NPCID|67540| |NAME|Crush| |LVL|Special| |ABIL|133254| |ST|(npc:67540), formerly a Legacy challenge in Warlords of Draenor, resembles (npc:34797) from Trial of the Crusader and is a relatively easy fight. He does a jump back and charges with (spell:133254). Just move out of the way and whack him while he's stunned.|	
|NPCID|67678| |NAME|Dark Summoner| |LVL|Special| |ABIL|133499,125212,133465,133426,133427| |ST|The (npc:67678), formerly a Rank 7 brawl in Warlords of Draenor, is a ghost that starts the fight with (spell:133499) and follows you around the arena while casting (spell:125212) and hitting you with weak melee attacks. He will also cast (spell:133465). These (npc:67664) spawn at random locations in the arena and fixate on you and if they touch you they kill you in one or two hits. When the fight starts you are buffed with (spell:133426), a frontal cone light, enabling you to stop the (npc:67664) with (spell:133427) and damaging them without getting killed.<br/><br/>Killing the (npc:67664) removes (spell:133499) for a short period of time allowing you to damage the (npc:67678). Kiting around the arena, stacking and lining up the (npc:67664) to stop them all with (spell:133426) is crucial, but be extra careful, as they can spawn right next to you or behind you and their melee range is quite large (almost unforgivably large). The (npc:67664) are succeptible to stuns, roots, and knockbacks.|	
|NPCID|67451| |NAME|Deeken| |LVL|Special| |ABIL|133156,133169| |ST|This was formerly a Legacy Challenge in Warlords of Draenor. Electricity moves across the floor while you fight (npc:67451) dealing (spell:133156) damage. Look for the openings in the path and avoid the electricity. Jumping over it seemed to work but standing in it is ill-advised. (npc:67451) will also use (spell:133169) that may knock you back into electricity.|	
|NPCID|68255| |NAME|Dippy| |LVL|Special| |ABIL|134537,134536| |ST|This was a middle ranked fight in Warlords of Draenor and it's a fairly easy one. (npc:68255) is fast and weak while (npc:70648) is slow but strong. Focus on killing (npc:68255) first and avoid (npc:70648) and you should be fine. Everytime you hit either one, you will knock them back and interrupt their cast of (spell:134537). If either hits you with (spell:134537), yea, you guessed it -- you die!|	
|NPCID|70648| |NAME|Doopy| |LVL|Special| |ABIL|134537,134536| |ST|This was a middle ranked fight in Warlords of Draenor and it's a fairly easy one. (npc:68255) is fast and weak while (npc:70648) is slow but strong. Focus on killing (npc:68255) first and avoid (npc:70648) and you should be fine. Everytime you hit either one, you will knock them back and interrupt their cast of (spell:134537). If either hits you with (spell:134537), yea, you guessed it -- you die!|	
|NPCID|67483| |NAME|Disruptron Mk. 3R-Alpha| |LVL|Special| |ABIL|135621| |ST|This fight, formerly a Legacy Challenge in Warlords of Draenor, will push your awareness skills to the limit. As you engage (npc:67483), three lasers spawn on the ground; two moving horizontally, and one moving vertically; each of them fading in and out as they move across the floor. When the laser is fading out, it will do little to no damage, and when it is at it's brightest it will more or less one-shot you (the timing on moving through the lasers is very strict though, so do this with caution), you can also jump over them (the latter being the recommend option and the least likely to get you killed).<br/><br/>Futhermore, there are cannons shooting multiple pulses in a straight line that deal approximately a large amount of physical damage. The cannons at the sides shoot two-three (covering mostly a 90 degree area; shooting roughly 33 and 66 degrees for the (npc:67479) and 0, 45, and 90 for the (npc:67478)), while the (npc:67480) in the center of the arena shoots five. (npc:67483) will activate these cannons one by one during the fight and will announce it in yells for each one. A red arrow will indicate which cannon is active and firing. When you reach ~30% the cannons will start to shoot pulses more rapidly.<br/><br/>(npc:67483) will also cast (spell:135621) that can either be outranged or you can use stuns or knockbacks to interrupt it.<br/><br/>In the Alliance encounter you can negate the single vertical line if you hug the north wall, whereas in the Horde encounter you can negate every second horizontal line on the south or north end, as the lasers stop a few yards before they reach the wall. You can also make clever use of (spell:1706) to avoid the lasers entirely, and there are certain static points in the arena area where casters can stand (with levitate) and not take any hits from the disruptor cannons - if you stand at the very end of the wall away from the flames of death on enrage, just a few steps away from the center of the wall, you will be able to dodge everything without moving or at the very least only side-step slightly back and forth. This latter trick has been working since patch 5.3 and the lightning fields will not kill you when they move underneath you. If it has been removed for Patch 7.1.5 needs confirmation.
|NPCID|70739| |NAME|Doctor FIST| |LVL|Special| |ABIL|141041,141100,141102,141103,141104| |ST|(npc:70739), formerly a Rank 6 brawl in Warlords of Draenor, has a wide range of abilities, and while they won't one-shot you, they will pack a decent punch if you're struck. The first four: (spell:141041), (spell:141100), (spell:141102), and (spell:141103); are cone effect attacks in front of the boss. The last one, (spell:141104), is a full 360 degrees within a 20 yard radius around the boss, which in all likelihood, will one-shot you from the second cast and onwards, as it increases damage dealt by 100% for each cast. All the abilities are clearly marked on the ground and the effect will appear with a dust-like graphic, so it's easy to tell if you're in the wrong spot. The best strategy is to hug the boss and either run through him when he casts or side-step the Left Hook, Right Hook, Bodyblow, or Uppercut, and then run out of Hammer Fist.|	
|NPCID|67485| |NAME|Dominika the Illusionist| |LVL|Special| |ABIL|133129,133123| |ST|(npc:67485), formerly a Rank 4 brawl in Warlords of Draenor, is a mage that summons illusions every time she is hit. (npc:67485) and her illusions cast (spell:133129). This makes it pretty easy for ranged classes to control the speed of the fight, casting a few select nukes, but harder for melee. Illusions have very low health and die in one hit. Cleave damage is a great way to deal with the illusions. Illusion deaths also trigger abilities such as (spell:34428), so remember to make clever use of your defensive cooldowns, glyphs, and healing abilities if the damage gets too overwhelming.|	
|NPCID|67596| |NAME|Fjoll| |LVL|Special| |ABIL|133346,133332,133344,133292,133289,79894| |ST|(npc:67596) is an undead vrykul who casts (spell:133346) and tries to knock you into them with (spell:133332). Beyond this he will be casting (spell:133344), which you can interrupt, and summon (spell:133292) that deal shadowflame damage (spell:133289). Lastly, he casts (spell:79894), which may result in you getting pulled on top of a (spell:133346).|	
|NPCID|67524| |NAME|Riddoh| |LVL|Special| |ABIL|133213,133227,133308,133296| |ST|(npc:67524), formerly a Legacy Challenge in Warlords of Draenor, is a giant with (npc:67525) sitting on its back, a reference to Hodor and Brandon Stark from the popular American fantasy drama television series Game of Thrones. This was formerly a Rank 2 brawl in Warlords of Draenor. Avoid (npc:67525)'s (spell:133213) and move out of the (spell:133227) (the landmines form a C on the ground, allowing you to move out safely). (npc:67524) casts (spell:133308) and upon (npc:67525)'s death he will get quite upset and turn into (spell:133296). The fight is rather simple - don't stand on mines, dodge the sticks of dynamite, kill (npc:67524) followed by (npc:67525).|	
