|NPCID|68257| |NAME|Goredome| |LVL|Special| |ABIL|142587| |ST|(npc:68257), formerly a Rank 1 brawl in Warlords of Draenor, is a shoveltusk, similar to the ones in Howling Fjord. It will cast (spell:142587) on top of you, indicated by a red circle on the ground and an arrow in the air, charging up for a few seconds, then rushing towards you. This ability will one-shot you and has to be dodged. It hits for weak melee damage and has no other gimmicks to it.|	
|NPCID|70659| |NAME|Hexos| |LVL|Special| |ABIL|140849,140834| |ST|(npc:70659), formerly a Legacy challenge in Warlords of Draenor, is themed heavily on the game Super Hexagon, an action twitch game developed by Terry Cavanagh. He attaches himself to your character's face, roots you in place with (spell:140849), and begins a two minute channel, casting no other abilities (or melee attacking) for the duration of the match. You can rotate freely and always have facing on (npc:70659) no matter what. Bright purple hexagonal patterns, or (spell:140834)s, will then start to converge on you. If any of the lines hits (npc:70659), you die instantly.<br/><br/>Since (npc:70659) is always in front of your face, this basically means that as the patterns approach, you need to constantly be turning to face the empty spot - just like the game the fight is based on. This would be tricky enough on its own, but (npc:70659) still needs to be killed, meaning that you need to perform your damage rotation the entire time you're spinning to survive the death planes. You basically can't take your eyes off the battlefield, so make sure you know your cooldowns and timers by heart!<br/><br/>Playing one of the Chipzel tracks from the original game may add to the overall experience of this fight. Also, rotate your camera straight down and spin yourself with the the mouse while you perform your damage rotation. Do not let the pink beams hit you in the face when they converge on you. This may take some practice and getting used to, but steering (npc:70659) through the maze is not the "objective."|	
|NPCID|68253| |NAME|Ixx| |LVL|Special| |ABIL|134777| |ST|(npc:68253), formerly a Rank 3 brawl in Warlords of Draenor, resembles (npc:15370) from Ruins of Ahn'Qiraj. It has a large health pool, but starts the fight at 20%. It has only one ability, but it's a quite lethal (spell:134777), a frontal cone attack, which has to be avoided. The strategy is quite simple, stay as close to the centre of its hitbox as possible, allowing you to run straight through it when the cast for (spell:134777) starts.|	
|NPCID|68377| |NAME|Leona Earthwind| |LVL|Special| |ABIL|134741,129888,134743| |ST|(npc:68377), formerly a Legacy Challenge in Warlords of Draenor, is a night elf druid that casts nature-like spells such as (spell:134741) and (spell:129888). She also summons (npc:68383) with (spell:134743). You can interrupt her (spell:134741) and silence or stun her while she is casting (spell:134743). The (npc:68383) does melee damage and if she allows to summon multiples the damage may get overwhelming.|	
|NPCID|68254| |NAME|King Kulaka| |LVL|Special| |ABIL|44531| |ST|(npc:68254), formerly a Rank 2 brawl in Warlords of Draenor, is a huge devilsaur and a simple tank-and-spank fight. His only ability is (spell:44531) allowing him to chase you down easily, and on top of this he hits extremely hard. Kite him around if possible and make good use of your defensive cooldowns if you're in for a beating. Pop all your offensive cooldowns and hope it will be enough before he eats you up whole!|	
|NPCID|67269| |NAME|Kirrawk| |LVL|Special| |ABIL|97474,135234,132670,132673| |ST|(npc:67269), formerly a Rank 2 brawl in Warlords of Draenor, is an Arrakoa shaman. He will make good use of his arsenal of shaman abilities and spam you with (spell:97474), which you can interrupt, and should interrupt as much as possible. Additionally, he will cast (spell:135234) on himself. He will also use (spell:132670) to summon a (npc:54467) that will follow you around and suck you up into the air if it touches you. Avoid getting hit by this as (npc:67269) will start to cast (spell:132673), which can be quite lethal. Instead, kite the (npc:54467) on top of (npc:67269) and let him get a taste of his own medicine.|
|NPCID|67571| |NAME|Millhouse Manastorm| |LVL|Special| |ABIL|133654,133655,133398,133379,133650,134772| |ST|During the fight, (npc:67571), formerly a Legacy challenge in Warlords of Draenor, will be casting (spell:133654) and (spell:133655) at you. These do not hit very hard. In addition, he will spawn two (npc:67612). These will channel in the direction of (npc:67571), granting stacks of (spell:133379), which increases damage done. To prevent these from reaching (npc:67571), you can either destroy the crystal or block the channel by standing between the crystal and (npc:67571), granting the buff to your instead. (npc:67571) has a very large health pool, so you will need get as many stacks from (spell:133379) as possible. In addition, if (npc:67571) reaches 100 stacks, he will cast his (spell:133650), killing you. Lastly, he will knock you back with (spell:134772) if you stand too close to him.<br/><br/>So, this fight is all about minimizing the stacks (npc:67571) receives while maximizing the amount you receive. When possible, blocking both beams is preferred. Blocking one and destroying the other is also a viable option, but doing this too many times will be hard on the damage check. It is very important not to lose your (spell:133379) stacks, as you will not have the damage necessary to defeat him without it. When you hit 100 stacks or close to, pop all your cooldowns and potion and burn him down.|	
|NPCID|70616| |NAME|Mingus Diggs| |LVL|Special| |ABIL|140754,140751,140748,140746,142807,140758| |ST|This was a high ranked fight back in Warlords of Draenor and it evolves around the four statues: (npc:70617), (npc:70618), (npc:70619), and (npc:70620), one standing in each corner of the Brawler's Ring. Each statue will start stacking a debuff on you: (spell:140754), (spell:140751), (spell:140748), and (spell:140746) that gets more and more painful and stacks really fast; about 2 stacks a second. The basic idea is that if you stand next to one of them, it will deactivate and stop casting everything so you can drop off the debuff, thus taking less damage. (npc:70616) will also be chasing you around and hitting you with his shovel for weak melee damage. He is immune to damage through (spell:142807) till the four statues are killed.<br/><br/>The strategy is quite simple -- manage the stacking debuffs by running around dropping them as needed. As ranged you are able to dps the statues while deactivating another debuff; utilize this to your advantage. Melee need to manage debuffs a bit closer or risk taking added damage; ideally you need to keep bouncing between statues to minimize debuff stacks. Abilities like (spell:31224), (spell:45438), etc., are useful to drop the debuff stack when damage gets overwhelming. Monks can use (spell:45438) on two statues and only rely on bouncing back and forth between the remaining two.|
|NPCID|71081| |NAME|Mecha-Bruce| |LVL|Special| |ABIL|142795,142769,142756,142788,135340| |ST|(npc:71081), formerly a Card Challenge in Warlords of Draenor, attacks like ordinary Bruce, except he will use an ability called (spell:142795), which he will channel for a few seconds, and afterwards he will use (spell:142769), which will stun your character for 3 seconds. He will use (spell:142756) every other chomp phase, so he will chomp, upgrade, chomp, chomp, upgrade, etc. Every upgrade makes him faster and stronger, so he will hit harder, move faster, attack faster, and channel his abilities faster. The longer the fight goes on, the more likely you will be chomped when he stuns you due to his insane speed.<br/><br/>Park (npc:71081) in a corner. When he starts to channel (spell:142756), run to the opposite corner to maximize the distance between the two of you after (spell:142769). Dodge (spell:142788) or suffer the audiences' taunts. He will not stun pets, always the player, but you can use pet taunts to let them get chomped.|	
|NPCID|68252| |NAME|Proboskus| |LVL|Special| |ABIL|124935,124860,47008| |ST|(npc:68252), formerly a Rank 6 brawl in Warlords of Draenor, is a large Water Strider with two major abilities. The first is (spell:124935), which you can and should interrupt or silence. The second is (spell:124860), which you have to dodge around. Lastly, (npc:68252) has his own enrage timer and goes (spell:47008) after approximately a minute.|	
|NPCID|70749| |NAME|Ro-Shambo| |LVL|Special| |ABIL|141206,141471,141463,141431,141467,141429| |ST|(npc:70749), formerly a Card Challenge brawl in Warlords of Draenor, is an amusing fight, to say the least. It's the Crawling Claw model, scaled up. Hang near the middle of the arena with him, because the gimmick of the fight only seems to trigger if you're near him. Every so often, (npc:70749) casts (spell:141206), giving you 5-6 seconds to choose one yourself in a vehicle-like interface that pops up. Get it wrong, and he unleashes the related power - scissors summons a giant, ridiculously painful pair of (npc:70873), rock summons a swarm of rolling (npc:70786)s, and paper summons (npc:70970).<br/><br/>BUT... If you win the round of rock-paper-scissors, (npc:70749) takes 500% damage for a few seconds afterward, and the power he unleashes is a joke (the (npc:70868) have less health, the (npc:70813) is much less dangerous, and (npc:70969) are, well, shredded). (npc:70749) has 12 million health, so you really want to go best out of three to win (read: get at least the first two rounds in your favor).|	
|NPCID|117208| |NAME|Seagull| |LVL|Special| |ABIL|233398,195561| |ST|Everyone's favorite trash mob from Eye of Azshara; (npc:117208) is here to mess everything up! It does relatively high melee damage through (spell:233398) and (spell:195561) that will disorient you.|	
|NPCID|68305| |NAME|Smash Hoofstomp| |LVL|Special| |ABIL|134624,134623,134650| |ST|(npc:68305), formerly a Rank 1 brawl in Warlords of Draenor, is guarded by two (npc:68306) sitting on his shoulders. When they die, they each provide a stack of (spell:134624) on (npc:68305). He will do (spell:134623) and also use (spell:134650) as a defensive measure. For the latter, attacks has to be made from behind. Overall, this is not a difficult encounter. Simply kill the goblins, then proceed to kill (npc:68305).|	
|NPCID|117179| |NAME|Strange Thing| |LVL|Special| |ABIL|233386,233313,233392,233527,231766| |ST|(npc:117179) casts (spell:233386), (spell:233313), and (spell:233392) spawning various adds such as (npc:117169) that fears, (npc:117206) that charges, and an army of (npc:117203)s. At the end of the fight will cast (spell:233527), which will turn your camera view upside down.|	
|NPCID|70983| |NAME|T440 Dual-Mode Robot| |LVL|Special| |ABIL|141395,141400,141411,141396,141401,141404| |ST|(npc:70983), formerly a Legacy Challenge in Warlords of Draenor, is a fight where you need to swap from melee to ranged, then back again every once in a while. If you are in melee range, it will be in (spell:141395) melee you. If you are at ranged, it will be in (spell:141400) and fire electric bolts about the room with (spell:141411) with increasing precision. The longer he is in either mode, the faster and stronger his attacks will get due to (spell:141396) or (spell:141401). At about 15-20 stacks this will start to get overwhelming for most classes. To clear its stacks you have to switch your range and force it to change mode. When it switches it does an (spell:141404) that deals a moderate amount of damage and stuns you for one second. If you're a melee class, you can stun it or use speed boosts to get it to swap to ranged mode. If you decide to do it entirely ranged or entirely melee, you have to eat two of those bursts as it will switch modes twice. If you can mitigate/negate the damage and/or heal it up, great!|	
|NPCID|70748| |NAME|Argh| |LVL|Special| |ABIL|141142,141061,142657,141139| |ST|You'll notice the 3 trampolines on the ground, bouncing three times in a row gives you (spell:141142) that increases your critical chance and damage on your next attack. The whole strategy here is to start on one side, and hop to the middle, then the last before hopping on to double stacked tables to smack (npc:70748), "The Lady", with your highest damage dealing attack. You don't have to go to the platform if you're a caster or ranged that doesn't need to be in melee range. Also, there is a bear named (npc:70750), he does (spell:141061) and (spell:142657), else he's just kinda there. Heal through his damage or absorb if you can. Otherwise just a bear. You will not be able stay on the platform for very long as (npc:70748) will (spell:141139) you off after a few seconds (yes, this is what "ladies" do, and it hits quite hard).<br/><br/>Note: Now that you know the strategy, you need to know about the trampolines, as they are quite tedious at first until you get used to them. When jumping on the trampoline you have about one second before it bounces you off in the direction you're facing, do NOT jump when already on it. Just hop on, face the next trampoline, and let it shoot you off.|	
|NPCID|70750| |NAME|Raaaargh| |LVL|Special| |ABIL|141142,141061,142657,141139| |ST|You'll notice the 3 trampolines on the ground, bouncing three times in a row gives you (spell:141142) that increases your critical chance and damage on your next attack. The whole strategy here is to start on one side, and hop to the middle, then the last before hopping on to double stacked tables to smack (npc:70748), "The Lady", with your highest damage dealing attack. You don't have to go to the platform if you're a caster or ranged that doesn't need to be in melee range. Also, there is a bear named (npc:70750), he does (spell:141061) and (spell:142657), else he's just kinda there. Heal through his damage or absorb if you can. Otherwise just a bear. You will not be able stay on the platform for very long as (npc:70748) will (spell:141139) you off after a few seconds (yes, this is what "ladies" do, and it hits quite hard).<br/><br/>Note: Now that you know the strategy, you need to know about the trampolines, as they are quite tedious at first until you get used to them. When jumping on the trampoline you have about one second before it bounces you off in the direction you're facing, do NOT jump when already on it. Just hop on, face the next trampoline, and let it shoot you off.|	
|NPCID|70733| |NAME|Tyson Sanders| |LVL|Special| |ABIL|141084,141129,141038,141252| |ST|(npc:70733), formerly a Rank 4 brawl in Warlords of Draenor, is fond of chickens. You are required to dance around to avoid these chickens while damaging him. He summons three types of chicken: 1) (npc:70731) are (spell:141084) and summons (spell:141129) on the ground, doing damage and knocking you back, 2) (npc:70732) does an AoE explosion with (spell:141038) after a few seconds (these are your main concern), and 3) (npc:69273) follows you around meleeing you for increasing damage through (spell:141252).|	
|NPCID|70666| |NAME|Ty'thar| |LVL|Special| |ABIL|140868,140862,140886| |ST|This was a low ranked Card Challenge in Warlords of Draenor and the basics to it are pretty simple and is exactly like the old game Punch-Out!!. (npc:70666) has a very distinct fighting style, and as part of his agreement with the Brawler's Guild, you have to follow his rules: 1) Face-to-face fist fighting, 2) No running around, and 3) Three knockdowns wins the fight. You avoid his jabs and punches by sidestepping left, right or back (either turn or strafe). If he throws left, move to the right, and vice versa, and if he stomps move back.|	
|NPCID|68250| |NAME|Unguloxx| |LVL|Special| |ABIL|| |ST|(npc:68250), formerly a Rank 6 brawl in Warlords of Draenor, is an adorable giraffe. It has no extraordinaire abilities or skills and can be dealt with as a simple tank and spank fight -- except the fact that it hits like a truck on steroids. You will need to stun or kite when the damage gets too overwhelming or use defensive cooldowns to mitigate the damage. It's either kill or be killed... by a giraffe!|	
|NPCID|67579| |NAME|Vian the Volatile| |LVL|Special| |ABIL|134740,133293,133607| |ST|(npc:67579), formerly a Rank 3 brawl in Warlords of Draenor, is a mogu with a desire for pyrotechnics. He summons moving fireballs called (spell:134740), he casts (spell:133293), as well as (spell:133607) which can be avoided by interrupting, stunning or moving out of the path. Your main priority is to avoid (spell:133607). Simply stepping aside a few yards does the trick. In addition to this, you need to avoid all the (spell:134740). As the fight drags on, there will be more and more of these in the arena and since (npc:67579) will always run after you (so that he is close to you for (spell:133607)), you need to control his position and should make him avoid the (spell:134740) as well, as otherwise, his spell casting speed will be increased.|	
|NPCID|68256| |NAME|Yikkan Izu| |LVL|Special| |ABIL|134789,134790,134795| |ST|(npc:68256), formerly a Rank 6 brawl in Warlords of Draenor, resembles (npc:23035) from Sethekk Halls and is surrounded by four (npc:68268). These will keep spawning four at a time, roughly every eight seconds. When you kill the ravens (npc:68256) will get a stack of (spell:134789) and enrage with (spell:134790) if it stacks to five, making the fight significantly harder to deal with. (npc:68256) will also cast (spell:134795), which you can interrupt or silence. You can kite, slow, root, and stun (npc:68256).<br/><br/>There appears to be some issues with the stacking (spell:134789) and the (spell:134790), enraging before five stacks. If you kill off one (npc:68268) and allow for the first stack of (spell:134789) to drop and then kill off the other and new birds as they spawn, this should make the brawl easier to deal with.|	
|NPCID|67518| |NAME|Zen'shar| |LVL|Special| |ABIL|133208,134772,133199| |ST|(npc:67518), formerly a Legacy Challenge in Warlords of Draenor, is a two phase encounter. In phase one you're fighting a swarm of (npc:67519) while (npc:67518) is immune to damage, but still casting (spell:133208) indicated by a purple circle on the ground. Running underneath (npc:67518) triggers (spell:134772). Cleave the (npc:67519) down as fast as you can.<br/><br/>This will push you into phase two where (npc:67518) is now active. You will still be dealing with (spell:133208) but also have to dodge an array of laser beams that will hit you with (spell:133199). While you're able to survive one hit of either, two consecutive will in all likelihood kill you. It is recommended to use cooldowns at the start to get into the last phase as quickly as possible, and from here on out it's only a matter of dancing!|	
